This paper deals with the efficient computation of probabilities of boolean expressions in the context of probabilistic databases. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and graph theory, which are common in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of conjunctive queries, which are a common topic in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the computation of probabilities, which is a common topic in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
